i am rotations officer for Celestial Empire. There are a number of lower level guilds rotating mobs, rotation board is on Seekers of Divinity board. (at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.wiberg.nu/~larsen01/phpBB2/index.php)">www.wiberg.nu/~larsen01/p...index.php)</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Guilds in the rotation are:<br>
celestial empire<br>
covenant of the wolf<br>
seekers of divinity<br>
legacy of the fallen (mainly the reformed eternal shadows just so you know)<br>
magus imperilaus magus (ok, spelling is wrong)<br>
comet noscet.<br>
an informal wudan twinks/friends/alts raid group (they probably joining rotation too soon i think)<br>
<br>
mobs being rotated are:<br>
cursed cycle srz temple<br>
ntov<br>
creator<br>
sleepers tomb<br>
king tormax / idol / aow<br>
cazic thule.<br>
<br>
not all the guilds are in those rotations (ie some guilds are working their way up to joining some of these rotations, some higher guilds don't do the lower level mobs) but broadly, these guilds have agreed to do the rotations.<br>
<br>
The parameters are pretty straight forward, 24 hours to kill, after which, free for all. About 75% of time the rotated mobs are killed withing 24 hours, so there is still plenty of opportunity to kill them while FFA if people need them.<br>
<br>
Does AD wish to join rotation for any of these mobs?<br>
I know most of these mobs are generally well below AD level mobs, reason i ask, from info i have recieved (although i can't personally verify it) AD have dropped some of these mobs recently.  <br>
If you wish to be part of any of these rotated mobs, it is easy, just have your rotation officer sign up to sod board and ask for acces to rotation forum. There are generally qualifiers for killing stuff, but don't think AD would really have to prove they can kill any of this stuff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
If you do not wish to be part of these rotations, can i ask please that you respect the agreed rotations set out here.  Rotations generallly seem to be the way that guilds work out contested spawns, and if it works on the AD/wudan / mim level, no reason why it can't work at our level too.<br>
<br>
PS: maybe i should have edited the first line. i don't mean to imply that any of the guilds i listed above are 'lower level guilds'.  I know each is uber in their own way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , don't want to bruise any egos.<br>
<br>
thanks for your time<br>
