I don't think I'm going to give you the answer you want but I'll try to give you our perspective on these mobs<br>
<br>
yes AD has dropped several of the mobs on that list somewhat recently (the past month?).. there are also some on that list we haven't touched in a long time<br>
<br>
All of those events you list are all pick up events for us, which means that generally they are unplanned, done by a small number of people, and done either before or after our main raiding time.  None of the mobs on that list are actually planned ahead of time, nor will we be adding them into our schedule again.<br>
<br>
I hope that as part of your rotation you'll allow whatever guilds mob we 'steal' that day to have another legit shot the next pop.  That's the best possible solution I can offer you and how other guilds have handled it in the past.<br>
<br>
Sorry that we can't join up into rotations with all of you, but it's hard enough rotating the current content we're doing.. those mobs you listed are just treated by us as FFA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(6/20/03 8:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My thoughts</span><hr size=1> I am posting here as an SoD officer, and its pretty hard to be impartial since I have plenty of friends in AD, but I am very dedicated to this guild.<br>
<br>
When we listed our rotation mob, we avoided placing mobs that can be done with 6 people with the exception of ST, because mobs like Zlandicar, Dozekar, Klandicar, Statue of Rallos Zek are too easy to farm with just a few people 2 boxing, that legislating a rotation on them would be very hard.<br>
<br>
Mobs like Tormax, however require a slightly bigger crew, even for a guild like AD, and I assume those take at least 15 or so, even for an elemental guild to kill, and are slightly easier to control.<br>
<br>
The main reason for a rotation, other than ensuring mobs are evenly shared is to be able to schedule your events.  Since AD has long since been the top guild on server, competition has been less of an issue, but its wonderful to be able to post a schedule for the week to allow people to plan ahead and make events.  Most of SoD's players aren't hardcore players like those found in AD, and being able to post a time for a mob is a great help for us.  <br>
<br>
Before we managed to get a rotation worked among the guilds in our tier, this was impossible - expecially with mobs having a +- 12 hour random timer associated with them, officers would have to check non stop on twinks when a mob would spawn, and then rush over and kill it as soon as we spotted it up, and it was very stressing, lead to many disputes, and often times our USA players would never make events because they'd never know when we'd end up killing anything.  <br>
<br>
An example that used to happen, is after checking non stop for Tormax during our prime raiding time (7-11 CET) we end up going after an alternative target, and right as people are preparing to log off, we notice Tormax spawning.  Before, we'd have to beg clerics to stay online perhaps past their planned bedtime and be late at work the next day, and get it killed RIGHT AWAY, or risk Reverant killing it during the night; and people would be in a horrible mood - with a rotation instead, we can say, heck, we got 24 hours to kill it, kill it tomorrow instead, nobody will touch it.  If we know on the other hand, that no 'prime' targets will live past USA late night time, it puts an entire different pressure on people's minds, and changes EQ from fun to a job.<br>
<br>
I understand that those mobs are beyond trivial for AD, and that probably at any time during the day they could field enough bots/players to kill them, but at least a mob like Cursed requires us to plan ahead.<br>
<br>
I understand that after a night of raiding, and perhaps wiping to new content, slaying trivial content for twinks, or perhaps getting some loot that recruits could use is therapeutic, but there's plenty of mobs that drop very good loot that are FFA - and any mob that is left up for longer than 24 hours, is of course FFA as well.<br>
<br>
While AD might end up killing less mob, if they randomly take them FFA when they are up than if they joined the rotation, it is far more damaging if mobs are killed FFA, because it can be an extreme morale killer for people to come in early from work expecting to do cursed, only to find that it died already.  MiM and Wudan, who both have a late night crew who goes after mobs, both agreed to respect mobs that are rotated by us, and go after them only when they become FFA, or go after different mobs.<br>
<br>
In the case that a specific loot is requrired, like for example a new warriors needs a Blade of Carnage, or a newly recruited melee needs primal, let us know and we are very willing to accomodate you in whatever way.  I would mention ST keys as well, but there's plenty of ST mobs that are FFA, and Sontolak is always up, and Zlandicar is perma farmed by some AD members, so I don't imagine that would be an issue.<br>
<br>
Both at a friends level and at a guild level me/SoD have a great relationship with AD -  I owe a lot of very good advice to plenty of friends, and those in AD who help us regularly we try to help in return or award them some of the loot we get which might be upgrades for them, and we try to help whenever we can on occasions like Ring Wars, AoW's, and I have no wish to ruin it in any way.<br>
<br>
The reason why its so important that we hopefully get this sorted out, is because a rotation depends on everyone complying, and while AD doesn't 'hog' those mobs, having a single rogue guild or group of people makes it very hard to enforce it, and more importantly to plan events. <br>
<br>
Anyway, sorry for this long and rambled post, but it took a lot of work to get Wudan, CE, MiM, ES (now Legacy of the Fallen) CN, Reverant (now not anymore) to agree to a rotation, and its very disappointing that the top guild on the server, perhaps the champion of rotations on this server wouldn't understand how important this is and try and encourage us instead of making it harder.<br>
<br>
Mearis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=somthor>somthor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 661<br> <font color=#333333>(6/20/03 9:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.iofthestorm.org/images/mok.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts</span><hr size=1> might = right <br>
